WEBVTT

00:11.302 --> 00:14.264
<i>Now, the story of a wealthy family</i>
<i>who lost everything</i>

00:14.347 --> 00:16.349
<i>and the one son who had no choice</i>

00:16.433 --> 00:18.101
<i>but to keep them all together.</i>

00:24.107 --> 00:25.859
<i>It's </i> Arrested Development.

00:31.239 --> 00:33.950
♪ <i>Just like the white-winged dove</i> ♪

00:34.034 --> 00:36.327
♪ <i>Sings a song</i>
<i>Sounds like she's singin'</i> ♪

00:36.870 --> 00:39.956
♪ <i>Ooh, baby, ooh, say ooh</i> ♪

00:40.040 --> 00:43.334
Oh!
Look who thinks they can wear white.

00:44.627 --> 00:45.962
You don't like this on me?

00:46.046 --> 00:48.965
Well, frankly,
it's hard to think about it

00:49.049 --> 00:52.010
over the sound of...
Was there a cat in here?

00:52.385 --> 00:55.096
That was my singing.
That's my talent.

00:55.180 --> 00:57.891
Oh. You'll be fine.

00:58.183 --> 01:01.311
Most people close their eyes
when they plug their ears.

01:02.729 --> 01:04.605
- It's not true.
- It is, Michael.

01:04.897 --> 01:07.525
It's very impossible not to.

01:09.527 --> 01:11.571
Well, I can. This should be my talent.

01:12.072 --> 01:14.657
The competition's in 40 seconds.
You still have nothing?

01:15.158 --> 01:17.410
I mean, I can see
that you're talking, but I just...

01:17.619 --> 01:18.870
I'm not a lip-reader.

01:19.913 --> 01:21.498
It'll be fine, honey.

01:21.581 --> 01:23.917
Maybe it'll be better
if you don't win this one.

01:24.167 --> 01:25.877
And you wouldn't be losing much,

01:25.960 --> 01:28.004
just a cruise with your grandmother.

01:33.676 --> 01:36.387
Okay, I heard that.
With Lindsay out of the competition

01:36.471 --> 01:37.639
and Buster gone missing,

01:38.014 --> 01:39.724
you're my only real competition, Michael.

01:39.933 --> 01:43.311
- What do you mean, "gone missing"?
- I... I told you.

01:44.646 --> 01:47.941
My plan. I took Buster off his leash,
and I brought him down to the beach.

01:48.024 --> 01:49.234
Don't worry, I told him how to swim.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.402
Hmm, my only thing is,
I have to figure out how

01:51.486 --> 01:53.738
to neutralize you, Michael.

01:54.322 --> 01:57.158
Oh, my... Oh, my God!

02:01.454 --> 02:02.288
That was a freebie.

02:04.374 --> 02:08.002
♪ <i>Just like the white-winged dove</i>
<i>Sings a song</i> ♪

02:08.086 --> 02:09.838
♪ <i>Sounds like she's singin'</i> ♪

02:09.919 --> 02:12.006
♪ <i>Ooh, ooh</i> ♪

02:12.090 --> 02:13.466
♪ <i>Ooh</i> ♪

02:18.805 --> 02:21.182
♪ <i>How much can you do?</i> ♪

02:22.934 --> 02:25.937
♪ <i>You lift and push and struggle</i> ♪

02:27.021 --> 02:30.024
♪ <i>When the foot's on the other shoe</i> ♪

02:31.067 --> 02:33.903
♪ <i>Just grab ahold and juggle</i> ♪

02:33.987 --> 02:36.781
♪ <i>All those balls in the air</i> ♪

02:37.740 --> 02:40.493
- Ha!
- ♪ <i>How hard can it be?</i> ♪

02:40.618 --> 02:43.371
♪ <i>So hard you're getting dizzy</i>
<i>Flip those balls ♪</i>

02:43.454 --> 02:45.039
♪ <i>In the air</i> ♪

02:45.373 --> 02:46.958
♪ <i>Keep those balls in the...</i> ♪

02:50.128 --> 02:52.297
But where did the confetti come from?

02:52.881 --> 02:56.718
From Michael's hat.
Honestly, these are so easy.

02:56.801 --> 02:59.554
That's it. I'm done. Ow.

03:05.143 --> 03:06.895
Abra...

03:08.521 --> 03:09.606
cadaver.

03:11.691 --> 03:13.985
What do you think? Can we chisel off
the hat of this thing

03:14.068 --> 03:15.737
without taking off the whole guy's head?

03:15.820 --> 03:18.198
Oh. Well, the competition's not over.

03:18.281 --> 03:20.825
We haven't even seen Lindsay.

03:20.909 --> 03:24.537
And you never will.
I want to save you the trouble

03:24.621 --> 03:27.832
of having to close your eyes
while plugging your ears.

03:28.082 --> 03:29.417
So how's this for my talent?

03:37.967 --> 03:38.927
Honestly, I don't know

03:39.010 --> 03:41.054
how Tap-Dancing Ghost doesn't take
the whole thing.

03:41.137 --> 03:43.014
Should we just throw a handkerchief
over this?

03:43.097 --> 03:45.642
Michael will do something impressive.
Don't worry.

03:49.771 --> 03:52.232
Buster went in the water.
He tried to swim. He almost drowned.

03:52.315 --> 03:53.399
Oh, my God! Do something!

03:53.483 --> 03:55.360
Save him!

03:55.443 --> 03:57.612
No, no, no, this isn't...
this isn't Michael's talent.

03:57.695 --> 03:59.113
This doesn't... This doesn't count!

03:59.197 --> 04:00.865
Who took off his gentleman collar?

04:04.118 --> 04:05.995
Oh, spirit of this dead bird,

04:06.412 --> 04:08.539
fly into my dead brother!

04:10.541 --> 04:12.961
Oh!

04:13.211 --> 04:14.587
Oh!

04:14.671 --> 04:17.089
I'm not too bad at this thing.

04:17.173 --> 04:19.841
Well, we all know
who the hero is today.

04:20.218 --> 04:22.387
We have our new Mr. and Mrs. Bluth.

04:22.679 --> 04:26.266
Michael and Buster.
You're okay, honey.

04:26.349 --> 04:29.602
Mommy's here.
And as much juice as you want tonight.

04:30.436 --> 04:32.897
Tonight, you get juice.

04:39.779 --> 04:42.156
<i>It was the day of Buster's trial.</i>

04:42.240 --> 04:43.950
<i>And while the Bluth family was</i>

04:44.033 --> 04:45.785
<i>- feeling tense...</i>
- You okay?

04:45.868 --> 04:47.287
- Uh-uh.
<i>- ...they were hoping the same</i>

04:47.370 --> 04:50.498
<i>- was not true for their attorney.</i>
- Where is Dusty?

04:51.541 --> 04:53.459
Oh, he wants to make an entrance.

04:53.543 --> 04:57.046
I... I think he's gonna come in...
nice and relaxed.

04:57.130 --> 04:59.882
And thank you again
for being a team player on that one.

05:00.633 --> 05:02.593
Believe me, the guilt will fade.

05:03.177 --> 05:05.263
I mean, I've cheated on you
a thousand times.

05:05.346 --> 05:07.974
I mean, almost makes up
for the permanent damage

05:08.057 --> 05:09.517
you did to my endocrine system.

05:10.226 --> 05:12.770
- Oh, God! God!
- Uh-oh.

05:13.771 --> 05:15.189
- Easy.
- Oh, man.

05:15.773 --> 05:17.442
What a day!

05:17.525 --> 05:19.527
Sorry. Just... I heard my...

05:20.278 --> 05:21.779
my dad's in the hospital. Just...

05:21.863 --> 05:24.741
- No, don't worry about that.
- I didn't need this today.

05:24.824 --> 05:25.742
Don't worry about that.

05:25.825 --> 05:27.869
You need to focus
on your opening statement.

05:27.952 --> 05:29.329
I go first? You said I was second.

05:29.412 --> 05:30.663
I'm not ready!

05:30.747 --> 05:32.290
You <i>are </i> second.

05:32.373 --> 05:36.377
All rise for the Honorable
Judge Spencer Stanley presiding.

05:39.505 --> 05:42.258
- Please be seated.
- I cannot wait

05:42.342 --> 05:44.344
to see her reaction when she sees him.

05:51.100 --> 05:52.560
You cut your hair.

05:53.353 --> 05:54.812
Eh. Yeah.

05:55.313 --> 05:57.607
Does she look rattled to you?

05:58.941 --> 06:00.485
<i> And soon, Michael arrived,</i>

06:00.568 --> 06:03.112
<i>just in time for the opening argument.</i>

06:03.196 --> 06:07.450
...the defense will probably
have you review a video, the one here,

06:09.077 --> 06:11.496
where they'll claim
that he had merely approached

06:11.579 --> 06:13.331
and discovered a body on the stairs,

06:13.414 --> 06:16.417
and then claim
it miraculously disappeared.

06:16.876 --> 06:17.794
It did.

06:17.877 --> 06:20.129
And so, it would seem that it did.

06:20.838 --> 06:25.051
Unless a closer look was made
of the time code.

06:25.885 --> 06:28.638
We'll learn that the gap

06:28.721 --> 06:32.725
was the result of Buster trying
to destroy the evidence.

06:33.559 --> 06:36.646
And we'll also review footage
of the same stair car

06:36.729 --> 06:38.064
on a bluff over the ocean

06:38.147 --> 06:41.192
and a man who appears to be Mr. Bluth

06:41.776 --> 06:46.531
tossing what appears
to be Ms. Austero into the surf.

06:48.658 --> 06:50.493
Let's remember why we're all here.

06:50.785 --> 06:52.537
To honor the life

06:52.620 --> 06:54.247
of the most charitable,

06:54.330 --> 06:58.042
vibrant, balanced,
beautiful woman named Lucille

06:58.126 --> 06:59.752
this town has ever known.

06:59.836 --> 07:01.754
Burn.

07:01.838 --> 07:04.132
It's just that my mother's name
is Lucille as well,

07:04.215 --> 07:07.301
- so the... the burn was on her.
<i>- </i> I'll allow the burn.

07:07.385 --> 07:09.971
Mr. Radler,
you may begin your opening argument

07:10.054 --> 07:11.806
- for the defense.
- I... I know.

07:14.600 --> 07:16.978
- Oh!
<i>- Things were off to a bad start.</i>

07:17.061 --> 07:18.896
<i>- But on the plus side...</i>
- If you find that funny,

07:18.980 --> 07:21.399
wait till you hear
the defense's opening argument.

07:21.482 --> 07:23.526
<i>...Dusty got the laugh he'd hoped for</i>

07:23.609 --> 07:25.736
<i>at the start of his defense.</i>

07:26.320 --> 07:29.157
Uh, I... I didn't know
about the videotape.

07:29.240 --> 07:30.491
So, I mean, what...

07:30.575 --> 07:34.287
- If you'll... ...please...
- I... I'm...

07:34.370 --> 07:36.998
Hmm. Yeah.

07:37.331 --> 07:39.917
You can just see
he... he's throwing the body

07:40.001 --> 07:42.128
right off the cliff,
so everyone's like, "Uh..."

07:42.211 --> 07:45.465
"I mean, what else could it be?"

07:46.591 --> 07:49.260
I didn't even know
you could use videotape. Um...

07:49.343 --> 07:51.137
<i>But to the Bluths' surprise,</i>

07:51.220 --> 07:53.973
<i>the DA didn't immediately call
for a mistrial.</i>

07:54.348 --> 07:55.892
I'm feeling
like people are judging me,

07:55.975 --> 07:59.020
and it's just not making me feel
that great.

07:59.979 --> 08:02.064
I... I feel like I got, like, totally

08:02.148 --> 08:03.816
the hard part of this case.

08:04.108 --> 08:07.153
- What the hell is going on?
<i>- Although she did show</i>

08:07.236 --> 08:09.447
<i>uncommon empathy
to the opposing counsel.</i>

08:09.530 --> 08:11.491
You can do it. You're ready.

08:13.034 --> 08:14.494
Everything go okay last night?

08:15.203 --> 08:17.288
I think I made a terrible mistake.

08:17.497 --> 08:18.998
<i>In fact, she had,</i>

08:19.081 --> 08:21.042
<i>as, the night before, while believing</i>

08:21.125 --> 08:24.045
<i>she was paying a carnal visit to Dusty...</i>

08:24.128 --> 08:25.838
Oh, it's so dark in here.

08:28.174 --> 08:30.593
Hello?

08:31.093 --> 08:33.971
I can hear you breathing.

08:34.138 --> 08:37.058
Oh,
so you <i>did </i> know I was coming.

08:37.975 --> 08:40.977
Good for you, getting a head start.

08:42.145 --> 08:44.190
And speaking of that...

08:44.273 --> 08:47.151
<i>But, had the lights been on,</i>
<i>Lucille would have discovered</i>

08:47.235 --> 08:49.904
<i>that the tubes and other accoutrements
weren't there</i>

08:49.987 --> 08:51.864
<i>for Dusty's erotic entertainment...</i>

08:52.448 --> 08:54.367
<i>...but were instead the implements</i>

08:54.450 --> 08:57.161
<i>That kept Dusty's
centenarian father alive.</i>

08:57.245 --> 09:00.331
So, Lottie is his ex?

09:00.414 --> 09:03.167
- Stepmom.
- I really appreciate this, Lottie.

09:03.251 --> 09:06.420
Please. I've known you since you were 30!

09:07.046 --> 09:08.673
And you can call me "Mom."

09:09.840 --> 09:10.716
Mom.

09:11.175 --> 09:13.261
If... If the judge will allow it,

09:13.469 --> 09:15.805
permission to hug the defense counsel.

09:19.976 --> 09:21.936
Hell yeah. Let's get the hug on.

09:22.019 --> 09:23.896
Yeah! Yeah!

09:23.980 --> 09:25.606
Aw.

09:25.690 --> 09:28.025
Oh! My baby!

09:28.109 --> 09:31.487
<i>It would've been a great ending</i>
<i>for a feel-good movie,</i>

09:31.571 --> 09:34.448
<i>but it was a horrible beginning
for a gruesome murder trial.</i>

09:34.532 --> 09:36.617
What a baby!

09:36.701 --> 09:38.494
Shut up, murderer!

09:38.578 --> 09:40.246
Well, he is. Clearly is.

09:40.329 --> 09:41.956
<i>And during a break in both the trial</i>

09:42.290 --> 09:46.627
<i>and the hug of the opposing attorneys,
Lucille caught up with Dusty.</i>

09:47.044 --> 09:48.879
I was a little nervous.

09:49.088 --> 09:52.842
For my first murder trial, though,
my first anything trial, not bad, right?

09:53.301 --> 09:54.802
That was humiliating.

09:54.885 --> 09:57.221
I thought Lottie was your <i>ex-wife.</i>

09:57.597 --> 10:00.516
Nah. I mean, she's a little old for me,
don't you think?

10:00.600 --> 10:02.435
She's, like... ...your age.

10:03.519 --> 10:07.023
Look, I'm sorry. Maybe I wasn't clear
about our relationship.

10:07.815 --> 10:10.109
Uh, are you super mad at me?

10:10.192 --> 10:12.695
Oh, for God's sakes,
stop talking like a child.

10:12.778 --> 10:14.071
I mean, how old are you?

10:14.363 --> 10:16.657
- Fifty-six and a half.
- Jesus!

10:16.741 --> 10:18.075
Pull yourself together.

10:18.159 --> 10:19.285
Absolutely.

10:19.368 --> 10:21.162
Not gonna let that ruin my recess.

10:23.289 --> 10:26.792
There you are. Okay.
Now, Mom, what in the hell was that?

10:26.876 --> 10:28.461
I thought this was Dustin Radler,

10:28.878 --> 10:30.296
the fierce trial attorney,

10:30.379 --> 10:32.548
the only one who's ever beaten Lottie.

10:32.632 --> 10:35.551
Well, as it turns out,
the Dustin Radler I've been with...

10:35.635 --> 10:36.636
is his son.

10:37.094 --> 10:39.305
Oh, my God, he's a motherboy.

10:39.513 --> 10:41.515
There were...
There were no hints before today?

10:41.599 --> 10:44.268
Just that I only ever seem
to create or attract them.

10:45.603 --> 10:47.730
You got us into this mess.
What are you gonna do?

10:48.147 --> 10:50.524
All right. I made an awful choice,

10:50.608 --> 10:53.944
but did I give you a hard time
when you gave all our life rights

10:54.028 --> 10:56.656
to Imagine Films to make some TV show?

10:56.739 --> 10:59.992
- That was somewhat amiss of you.
- Yes, you did.

11:00.076 --> 11:03.871
As it turns out, nothing came
of that project, which I predicted.

11:03.954 --> 11:05.831
Just like I predicted your bet

11:05.915 --> 11:09.335
on the DA calling a mistrial
wasn't exactly beating the odds.

11:09.418 --> 11:11.337
- She offered him gum.
- Okay, I hired

11:11.420 --> 11:14.924
a completely incompetent lawyer
and put my son's life in the hands

11:15.007 --> 11:17.843
of a moron, and I know
what you want me to say, Michael.

11:17.927 --> 11:20.638
Okay, I'll say it... My bad!

11:22.973 --> 11:27.061
Wow. I don't think
that I have heard you apologize since, um,

11:27.520 --> 11:29.939
uh, since people used to use
that phrase to apologize.

11:30.022 --> 11:31.982
Okay, well,
I think we may have to beg the judge

11:32.066 --> 11:33.651
- to declare a mistrial.
- No.

11:33.734 --> 11:36.654
We have to do this now
while they still don't have a body.

11:37.321 --> 11:40.366
It's our best chance for acquittal.
We'll work with what we have.

11:40.449 --> 11:43.536
Maybe her maternal instincts will kick in,

11:43.619 --> 11:46.038
and we'll benefit
from her being his stepmother.

11:46.122 --> 11:49.041
Yeah, I don't know about that.
He's not a child, after all.

11:51.252 --> 11:53.295
It occurs to me that he may not come back
from recess

11:53.379 --> 11:54.880
unless he hears a bell. I'll get him.

12:00.845 --> 12:02.596
<i>As the trial was continuing,</i>

12:02.680 --> 12:05.391
<i>Dusty was desperate</i>
<i>for </i> any <i>kind of witness.</i>

12:05.474 --> 12:07.643
- <i>...Guys and Dolls...</i>
<i>- Even one that came</i>

12:07.727 --> 12:09.603
<i>- with a headshot.</i>
- I was more than interested

12:09.687 --> 12:11.856
to try out to be one
of the character witnesses

12:11.939 --> 12:13.524
in Buster's trial.

12:14.233 --> 12:17.153
- Thank you for offering.
- That's very nice.

12:17.236 --> 12:19.905
Oh, please. I know the Buster character
better than anyone.

12:20.197 --> 12:22.700
I could play Buster with one arm
tied behind my back.

12:22.783 --> 12:26.454
In fact, I've played Buster
with <i>two </i> arms tied behind my back.

12:26.537 --> 12:28.038
I was handcuffed.

12:28.873 --> 12:31.125
Well, this is...
They're buying it!

12:31.208 --> 12:34.503
- Now, that's a witness.
- Um, we don't need you to play Buster

12:34.587 --> 12:37.381
on the stand,
more just talk about him as a person.

12:38.299 --> 12:40.217
Oh. Well,

12:40.426 --> 12:43.137
you don't think
I'd be more appealing as the accused?

12:43.220 --> 12:46.140
I mean,
the Buster <i>I </i> played could never kill.

12:46.307 --> 12:47.141
Yeah, it's...

12:47.224 --> 12:49.602
it's really not an acting job, man.
I can't...

12:49.685 --> 12:51.854
Yes, yes, just... don't push.
I get it.

12:51.937 --> 12:55.149
Just tell the story the way
you told it to me earlier today.

12:55.232 --> 12:57.777
Beginning with what you were doing
the night of the murder.

12:58.027 --> 12:59.653
<i>Alleged </i> murder. Alleged.

12:59.945 --> 13:00.863
Yes, yes.

13:02.490 --> 13:05.534
It was Cinco... de Cuatro!

13:05.618 --> 13:08.120
No, no, no,
I'm... I'm gonna stop you there.

13:08.204 --> 13:09.580
- I still feel you're acting.
- Really?

13:09.914 --> 13:10.956
- A little. I do.
- Huh.

13:11.040 --> 13:13.918
So, just no script at all?
Just vérité? Okay.

13:14.001 --> 13:15.836
Well, uh, here it is with nothing.

13:16.712 --> 13:19.298
I needed somebody to play a part in my...

13:19.548 --> 13:24.136
<i>Fantastic...</i> for legal purposes,
I can't say the rest of it... musical,

13:24.220 --> 13:26.555
and Buster happily filled in.

13:26.639 --> 13:29.517
<i>Well, "happily"</i>
<i>might have been an overstatement.</i>

13:29.600 --> 13:31.227
I've got a show to do in ten minutes,

13:31.310 --> 13:33.854
and I haven't got a Thing to wear...
this Thing suit.

13:33.938 --> 13:35.731
I gotta find Lucille 2.
I gotta give her pictures.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.149
I don't know the songs.

13:37.233 --> 13:39.151
You're a monster.
You don't have to be any good.

13:39.235 --> 13:41.403
What?

13:41.487 --> 13:45.199
So, you're saying <i>Buster </i> was performing
as the rock monster

13:45.282 --> 13:48.369
when the murder allegedly took place?
Is that true, Buster?

13:48.452 --> 13:51.539
That's what I told you.
He asked me to that night.

13:51.622 --> 13:53.290
And you'll confirm that on the stand?

13:54.166 --> 13:55.042
I will.

13:55.584 --> 13:59.004
And perhaps I'll do it
in an English accent!

13:59.672 --> 14:02.508
Nay, nay, I shan't.
I shall stick to the script.

14:02.716 --> 14:06.053
Not script. Nope. Vérité.
I have taken the note... vérité.

14:06.136 --> 14:07.179
- Yes, yes.
- Great.

14:07.263 --> 14:09.056
Now, I do wish I could do this gratis,

14:09.139 --> 14:11.684
but I'm having a bit
of a shelter crisis of late.

14:11.767 --> 14:13.519
- I hate to play hardball...
- I don't think

14:13.602 --> 14:15.312
that they pay witnesses.

14:15.396 --> 14:17.815
Hmm...

14:18.315 --> 14:19.275
Uh, unrelated...

14:19.358 --> 14:21.861
What happens to this room when you leave?

14:21.944 --> 14:23.863
Yeah, I think they lock it up at night.

14:24.321 --> 14:26.490
Damn it. Damn it, damn it, damn it.

14:30.870 --> 14:31.745
Damn it!

14:32.788 --> 14:33.747
I just...

14:34.915 --> 14:37.001
...need somewhere to s...

14:37.751 --> 14:41.463
All right, well, gentlemen,
thank you so much for your time.

14:42.798 --> 14:44.300
And I will be seeing you.

14:45.050 --> 14:46.385
<i>But back at the model home,</i>

