19:29.293 --> 19:31.378
He's not my friend anymore.

19:31.837 --> 19:33.505
Testifying against our family

19:33.589 --> 19:36.842
after all the times
I faked being surprised by him?

19:36.925 --> 19:39.219
<i>So Dusty went</i>
<i>after the witness's credibility.</i>

19:39.553 --> 19:43.307
Mr. Parmesan,
you say you're a master of disguises.

19:44.266 --> 19:46.476
How many looks
are you capable of creating?

19:48.312 --> 19:49.605
You asking me?

19:50.939 --> 19:52.149
I'm the judge.

19:54.067 --> 19:55.360
I'm Gene Parmesan.

19:55.444 --> 19:57.821
You say you had an undercover job,

19:57.905 --> 20:00.365
which means you must have left
the donkey punch stand.

20:00.449 --> 20:01.658
Isn't that correct?

20:02.034 --> 20:05.162
- Yes, it is.
<i>- </i> So you can't dispute my client's claim

20:05.412 --> 20:07.080
that he was dressed as the rock monster

20:07.164 --> 20:09.791
out on that floating barge
when the murder took place.

20:09.875 --> 20:12.836
Allegedly.
Allegedly took place.

20:13.045 --> 20:15.756
No, I did leave the donkey punch stand,

20:15.839 --> 20:18.425
uh, right before the play began.

20:18.508 --> 20:21.261
Mm-hmm. So how can you be sure

20:21.345 --> 20:23.847
that Buster <i>didn't </i> change
into the rock suit...

20:24.473 --> 20:25.891
as we've claimed?

20:26.934 --> 20:28.143
'Cause it was me.

20:29.269 --> 20:31.146
<i>After fighting with Lucille 2,</i>

20:31.230 --> 20:34.107
<i>Buster </i> did <i>end up</i>
<i>at the donkey punch stand...</i>

20:34.191 --> 20:35.651
It's punch, like the juice!

20:35.734 --> 20:37.486
Oh, I need some juice.

20:37.819 --> 20:39.446
<i>...but flew into a rage</i>

20:39.529 --> 20:41.281
<i>when he saw an old rival...</i>

20:41.365 --> 20:43.992
<i>...leaving behind</i>

20:44.076 --> 20:46.620
<i>the costume he was to be wearing, to a man</i>

20:46.703 --> 20:50.207
<i>who never said no to a costume
or a part-time job.</i>

20:50.290 --> 20:51.250
That's me.

20:52.459 --> 20:53.377
Yep.

20:53.585 --> 20:54.419
Wha...?

20:55.212 --> 20:57.256
<i>But while Gene</i>
<i>may have undermined</i>

20:57.339 --> 20:58.298
<i>- Buster's alibi...</i>
- Gene!

20:58.548 --> 21:01.385
<i>...back at the office,</i>
<i>George Michael was worried</i>

21:01.468 --> 21:03.470
<i>- about his dire situation...</i>
- Tickle, tickle.

21:03.553 --> 21:05.430
- Uncle Tobias, hi.
- Come on.

21:05.514 --> 21:07.975
<i>...when an even more dire one came</i>
<i>through the door.</i>

21:08.058 --> 21:09.768
Hey, what are you guys doing here?

21:09.851 --> 21:12.771
Well, our stay at the Spotted Palm

21:12.854 --> 21:16.275
came to a rather abrupt end
when "Bev" here...

21:16.358 --> 21:20.112
decided to look at her cellular telephone
without holding it at arm's length

21:20.195 --> 21:21.530
and putting on her readers first.

21:22.030 --> 21:24.324
- She blew our cover.
- Sorry, I keep forgetting

21:24.408 --> 21:26.118
that acting is my passion.

21:26.535 --> 21:27.911
It really ruined

21:27.995 --> 21:29.329
Annette's funeral,

21:29.413 --> 21:31.248
may she rest in peace.

21:31.707 --> 21:32.833
Maeby killed Annette?

21:33.458 --> 21:34.835
Where did we land with that?

21:34.918 --> 21:36.420
Uh... gore... she was gored.

21:36.503 --> 21:38.839
Yes. Gored in the running of the bulls.

21:38.922 --> 21:41.133
People were getting suspicious,
so it had to be somewhere

21:41.216 --> 21:42.551
where there wouldn't be a body.

21:42.676 --> 21:44.886
Or where an animal took off
with the body so fast...

21:44.970 --> 21:46.430
- That you couldn't get it back.
- Exactly.

21:46.513 --> 21:47.556
That was the idea.

21:47.639 --> 21:49.224
- Yep. Yes. Yep, yep.
- Yeah, yeah.

21:49.308 --> 21:51.935
Good. Well, if you guys were thinking
about staying here...

21:52.019 --> 21:54.521
Oh, thank you so much.
I told you he would come through!

21:54.604 --> 21:57.024
We cannot move in soon enough
for you.

21:57.107 --> 22:00.110
Some of our happiest days
as a family were spent here.

22:00.193 --> 22:01.862
It's not
an abandoned office anymore,

22:01.945 --> 22:03.905
so there are people doing work...
out there.

22:03.989 --> 22:08.452
Uh-huh. Well, if it's work you require,
I suppose we can act it off.

22:08.535 --> 22:10.829
- Yeah, that's going to be a problem.
- Well, surely,

22:10.912 --> 22:13.874
there must be some, uh,
in-house corporate training seminar

22:13.957 --> 22:16.835
we could do
or... or a sexual harassment video.

22:16.918 --> 22:19.755
I mean, I'm no Harvey Weinstein,
but I'm sure I could produce one.

22:20.297 --> 22:22.591
And I knew him. Did I tell you that story

22:22.674 --> 22:25.010
when Mr. Weinstein killed my ficus
in the '80s?

22:25.218 --> 22:26.720
When he came over to audition me for...

22:26.803 --> 22:30.265
Yes. We all know DeBrie Bardeaux snagged
a private audition

22:30.349 --> 22:31.767
with Harvey Weinstein.

