- Can you show me?
- Oh, sure.

23:31.076 --> 23:32.661
- God, yeah.
- No, your program?

23:33.120 --> 23:34.955
The... The code that you wrote?

23:35.956 --> 23:38.166
<i>George Michael was as surprised</i>

23:38.250 --> 23:42.421
<i>as the courtroom was about to be
when the DA introduced a witness</i>

23:42.504 --> 23:45.173
<i>who would turn the whole case upside down</i>

23:45.257 --> 23:47.092
<i>with a sense of the dramatic.</i>

23:48.176 --> 23:51.555
Okay. Now, Warden Gentles,
you recently paid a visit

23:51.638 --> 23:54.224
to the Hollywood motion picture
director Ron Howard

23:54.307 --> 23:56.226
with information about the Bluth family

23:56.309 --> 23:58.812
you thought was pertinent
to a project he was working on

23:58.895 --> 24:00.355
about the Bluth family.

24:00.439 --> 24:02.566
- Isn't that correct?
- That is correct.

24:02.649 --> 24:04.776
- Oh, my God.
- This had to do with an incident

24:04.860 --> 24:07.028
in Buster Bluth's past, correct?

24:07.112 --> 24:08.822
Yes. It is so.

24:08.905 --> 24:11.658
And how exactly did you acquire
this information?

24:11.908 --> 24:16.121
Well, if I may be eloquent,
straight from the horse's mouth.

24:16.204 --> 24:17.706
And who is the horse?

24:20.417 --> 24:21.543
Lucille Bluth,

24:22.419 --> 24:23.920
of course, of course.

24:24.629 --> 24:27.174
But all that information
on that case

24:27.257 --> 24:30.927
- had been sealed.
- Well, all seals can come loose

24:31.011 --> 24:31.970
with a little bit of...

24:32.679 --> 24:34.306
Gentles' pressuring.

24:35.474 --> 24:38.477
<i>And Lucille herself had been</i>
<i>so loosened.</i>

24:38.560 --> 24:42.647
<i>Some months earlier,
Lucille had enticed Warden Gentles</i>

24:42.731 --> 24:44.566
<i>to a private dinner in order</i>

24:44.649 --> 24:48.445
<i>to get her son Buster released
for a Second of July parade.</i>

24:48.945 --> 24:51.740
<i>And through the course
of a well-served meal,</i>

24:52.991 --> 24:55.911
<i>and even more frequently served
bottles of wine,</i>

24:56.328 --> 25:00.582
<i>Lucille rekindled a friendship
in order to ask for a favor.</i>

25:00.665 --> 25:03.001
<i>But as the afternoon turned into evening,</i>

25:03.084 --> 25:05.420
<i>intimate details issued forth</i>

25:05.504 --> 25:08.340
<i>from a now-drunken Lucille's mouth.</i>

25:08.757 --> 25:10.509
<i>Information extremely useful</i>

25:10.592 --> 25:14.137
<i>to a warden with ambitions
of a screenwriting career,</i>

25:14.221 --> 25:17.140
<i>who had heard
about an Imagine streaming series</i>

25:17.224 --> 25:19.601
<i>about this exact family.</i>

25:19.976 --> 25:23.146
<i>So, while Lucille got her son out
for a parade,</i>

25:23.230 --> 25:25.857
<i>Warden Gentles got a lot more.</i>

25:26.441 --> 25:29.110
<i>In fact,
the only thing guarded that evening</i>

25:29.569 --> 25:32.113
<i>was Warden Gentles' private trailer.</i>

25:32.989 --> 25:35.575
And you shared these stories
with Ron Howard?

25:35.659 --> 25:37.369
- <i>He did.</i>
- I did.

25:38.078 --> 25:41.248
Exhibit 3-A, <i>Making of a Monster.</i>

25:41.998 --> 25:45.210
I would like to play a clip
of the season finale.

25:46.962 --> 25:50.924
<i>And so, they played much</i>
<i>of the Imagine Bluth project.</i>

25:51.007 --> 25:52.926
<i>Now, remember, this is really rough.</i>

25:53.009 --> 25:56.221
<i>And our location guy was only able
